node.title: Victoria records 1,189 new COVID-19 cases and six deaths
node.description: There are now 11,051 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 605 people have died during the current outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,189\u00a0new\u00a0COVID-19 cases and six deaths.", "There are now 11,051\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 605\u00a0people have died during the current outbreak.", "There are 364\u00a0people in hospital with the virus in Victoria, of whom 80\u00a0are in intensive care and 44\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The health department said a further 39\u00a0people were in ICU but their infections were no longer considered active.", "The new cases were detected from 54,467\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 8,433\u00a0doses of vaccine administered at state-run sites yesterday, as well as more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "More to come.", "", "
Why we hear about some COVID-19 variants more than others
